#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/resource-management.md:1
msgid "Resource Management"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/resource-management.md:3
msgid "Use RAII for all resource acquisition and release (`raii`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/resource-management.md:5
msgid ""
"Resources — IRQ enable/disable state, port numbers, file handles, DMA "
"buffers, lock guards — must use the `Drop` trait for automatic cleanup. "
"Manual `enable()`/`disable()` call pairs are rejected."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/resource-management.md:11
msgid "// Good — RAII guard ensures IRQs are re-enabled\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/resource-management.md:19
msgid "// Bad — caller can forget to re-enable\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/resource-management.md:25
msgid ""
"Prefer lexical lifetimes so the Rust compiler inserts `drop` automatically, "
"rather than calling `drop()` manually. When the default drop order is "
"incorrect, use explicit `drop()` calls."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/resource-management.md:31
msgid "See also: PR [\\#164](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/pull/164)."
msgstr ""
